Maybe it could be a post-scarcity society in some united anthro Earth. Maybe their reason for not manually creating a bunch of humans when the technology to do so has obviously been around for quite a while is some moral one where they consider humans special and that making lab grown humans should only be used as a true last resort if humans actually go extinct. The only way I see a lost technology scenario working for this is if it's a post-apocalyptic story where just before the collapse Anon's pod had the necessary stuff to open it set up but before they actually got around to waking him up everything went to shit and then some tribe/raider group/whatever manages to wake him through some luck. There's definitely way more that could be done with this that I just can't think of right now, but hopefully I've given you a bit of inspiration.
